data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"type":"fabric_dataagent_preview_call_output","id":"fco_0b625e4bfb5551690069a7e5cbcf9881938cdc3d34934d923b","agent_reference":{"type":"agent_reference","name":"MyAgent","version":"239"},"response_id":"resp_0b625e4bfb5551690069a7e5ac92e88193bc82708c8a693d33","call_id":"call_c8b590073d04442a81f7528ee8ed7bb5","output":"{\"documents\":[{\"id\":\"7976adf8-5ea6-472e-8757-4eabf754283d\",\"content\":\"Here are some notable weather events recently recorded in Texas:\\n\\n- **High Wind (Dec 30\\u201331, 2007):** Gusts up to 71 mph were measured at the McDonald Observatory in the Davis Mountains, with high winds continuing into the early morning. No injuries or property damage were reported.\\n- **Heavy Snow (Dec 27\\u201328, 2007):** Four inches of snow fell near Perryton and Spearman, causing hazardous travel conditions.\\n- **Tornadoes (Dec 27, 2007):** Tornadoes were observed near Slaton/Southland and north of Lubbock. No reported damage.\\n- **Winter Weather Accident (Dec 27, 2007):** Snow and icy roads on US 287 near the Canadian River Bridge led to a fatal rollover accident, with one death and three injuries.\\n- **Winter Storm Accident (Dec 22, 2007):** Whiteout conditions from snow and wind east of Amarillo resulted in multiple major car accidents, causing over 150 injuries, two deaths, and more than $1.6 million in property damage.\\n\\nLet me know if you would like information for a different time period, location, or weather event type!\\n\",\"filepath\":\"fabric://response\",\"title\":\"Fabric Response for: weather events in Texas\",\"url\":\"https://msit.fabric.microsoft.com/groups/409e30ce-b2ad-4c80-a54d-d645227322e4/aiskills/98042b9e-11cb-422d-bd97-5873411aa7c8/stage/published/threads/thread_MuEWccMsL1Y7Q2gTKDe0QxyT/runs/run_fab0RN7GDuvl7m2LVt9lUWhDQ8vs/question/msg_YqQMPIJjBEdHT4AnUbPrWY7d/source/foundry\",\"metadata\":\"{\\u0022source\\u0022:\\u0022azure_fabric\\u0022,\\u0022query\\u0022:\\u0022weather events 